  "issue_title": "[Bug] `gitt config set` accepts arbitrary keys silently",
  "issue_body": "### Description\n\n`gitt config set KEY VALUE` performs no validation on `KEY`. Any string is accepted and persisted to `~/.gittensor/config.json`. Downstream readers use `config.get('wallet', 'default')` style lookups, so a misspelled key is silently dropped and the operator unknowingly continues with default values.\n\n### Repro\n\n```bash\ngitt config set wallet_name alice          # typo \u2014 should be `wallet`\ngitt config                                  # shows wallet_name=alice\ngitt issues view --id 1                     # uses wallet=default (silent fallback)\n```\n\nThe first command exits 0 with `Set wallet_name: alice` (green tick). No warning, no rejection, no hint that the key isn't recognized.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMatch `btcli config set`: typed options for each known key, raise `click.BadParameter` on unknown keys.\n\n```bash\ngitt config set --wallet alice              # OK\ngitt config set --wallet-name alice         # \u2192 \"Error: No such option: --wallet-name\"\n```\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`config_set` at [`gittensor/cli/main.py:96`](gittensor/cli/main.py#L96):\n```python\n@config_group.command('set')\n@click.argument('key', type=str)\n@click.argument('value', type=str)\ndef config_set(key: str, value: str):\n    ...\n    config[key] = value          # \u2190 any string, no whitelist\n```\n\nThe docstring lists \"Common keys\" (`wallet`, `hotkey`, `contract_address`, `ws_endpoint`, `network`) but does not enforce them.\n\n### Why this matters\n\n- Silent failure: the operator believes the change took effect (green confirmation) when it didn't.\n- Cross-command divergence: `gitt issues register` and `gitt miner post` both read this file. A typo'd key affects every subcommand consistently and silently.\n- Pattern mismatch: `btcli config set` exposes typed options for each setting; gittensor users coming from btcli expect the same UX.\n\n### Proposed fix\n\nReplace the positional `KEY VALUE` arguments with typed options, one per allowed key, mirroring `btcli config set`:\n\n### Notes\n\n- Backwards compatibility: existing `~/.gittensor/config.json` files keep working unchanged (only the *write* path is restricted; the *read* path still tolerates anything in the file).\n- `btcli config set` (`bittensor_cli`) already follows this pattern \u2014 `--wallet-name`, `--hotkey`, `--network`, `--safe-staking`, etc. are all explicit options.\n- Companion enhancement (separate PR if desired): align the recently-proposed `gitt config get <key>` (#803) and `gitt config unset <key>` (#804) to the same typed-option style so the whole `config` family is consistent.\n\n### Related\n\n- No prior filing on this \u2014 searched `config set whitelist | typed | arbitrary | validation`, all returned 0 hits.\n- Adjacent (different concern): #623 \"Consolidate duplicated CLI endpoint/config resolution logic\" (DRY refactor, not validation).\n- Adjacent companion PRs that don't address this: #803 (closed, `config get`), #804 (open, `config unset`).\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-29T20:24:24.000Z",
